I used Linode to host my SFTP Server. https://www.linode.com/

Requirements:

FTP - SFTP Server (I use Debian)
WinSCP Automation Files
PuttyGen or Generate keys with ssh-keygen.
Windows OS to use execute PowerShell Script.

Links:

WinSCP - https://winscp.net/download/WinSCP-5.19.6-Automation.zip
PuttyGen - https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/putty/latest.html  | https://the.earth.li/~sgtatham/putty/latest/w64/puttygen.exe
Windows OS
Linux (Debian or other prefered) https://www.debian.org/


You can alose use Filezilla FTP Server.

FileZilla: https://filezilla-project.org/download.php?type=server


Commands I use in Linux Server:

Get Server Fingerprint: ssh-keygen -lf /etc/ssh/ssh_host_rsa_key.pub
